OL,5,FThis week saw the disappearance of the
OL,6,FSmithsonian Channel. No doubt more will
OL,7,Ffollow before BBC Four becomes a
OL,8,Fstreaming service in the next 18 months
OL,9,For so.
OL,11,FPerhaps the recovery from the Covid
OL,12,Fpandemic is likely to help the big
OL,13,Fchannels too.
OL,15,FTV production was badly affected by
OL,16,FCovid restrictions. It led to shorter
OL,17,Fepisodes, shorter series and fewer
OL,18,Fprogrammes of outstanding note.
OL,3,CLinear TV still packing a punch
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G7/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35908
SC,0008
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F359A1675159471
OL,5,FThe lead-in times for some programmes
OL,6,Fand the gradual resumption of normal
OL,7,Fworking after legal restrictions ended
OL,8,Fmeans it took some time to get the
OL,9,Fsupply of new programmes fully back to
OL,10,Fnormal.
OL,12,FIt's time to celebrate the importance
OL,13,Fof the big linear channels properly and
OL,14,Fstop taking them for granted.
OL,3,CLinear TV still packing a punch
